rubrications.rubrication:
Nomina sacra; 
the word mәʿәraf;
a few lines (in both columns) in the incipit page of each text, divided into two, three or four groups, alternating with black lines (2 lines in fol. 6r, 9 lines on fol. 44r, 5 lines on fol. 64r, 8 lines on fol. 101r); the Canon tables; 
the incipits of the parts of the Introduction (fols. 6ra – 13va) and of the chapters of the Gospels;
the title of each Gospel; the chapters titles;
Ethiopic numerals of the “tituli”;
the horizontal dashes above and below Ethiopic numerals; 
elements of the punctuation signs;
name of Wälättä Mädḫәn, one of the donors(fol. 43vb, l.22); names of the church feasts in the upper margin of some fols. indicating the Gospel readings.

